==English==
===Etymology===
From Latinized {{Gr.}} [[Demetrius]], from [[Ancient Greek]]  '''[[Δημήτριος]]''' (''Demetrios'') "of or belonging to [[Demeter]]", from '''[[Δημήτηρ]]''' (''Demeter''), in Greek mythology the goddess of agriculture, mother of Persephone, from '''[[Δή]]''' (''De''), an early form of '''[[Γή]]''' (''Ge'') "earth" + '''[[μήτηρ]]''' (''meter'') "mother".

